Davis Water and WasteIndustries Inc said it has restated its earnings on a pre-stock split basis for fiscal 1987's third quarter and ninemonths ended January 31, which were reported March 10 on a postfour-for-three stock split basis.    The company said its earnings per share for the thirdquarter on a pre-split basis, converts to 16 cts from 12 ctspost-split, versus three cts pre-split from two cts post-splitfor fiscal 1986's third quarter.    For the nine months, Davis said, earnings per share wouldconvert to 77 cts and 44 cts for fiscal 1987 and 1986respectively, from 58 cts and 33 cts, respectively. Reuter&#3;